.TH "svc_rdma_encode_write_chunk" 9 "svc_rdma_encode_write_chunk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
svc_rdma_encode_write_chunk \- Encode one Write chunk
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" svc_rdma_encode_write_chunk
.BI "(struct svc_rdma_send_ctxt *sctxt "  ","
.BI "const struct svc_rdma_chunk *chunk "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sctxt" 12
Send context for the RPC Reply
.IP "chunk" 12
Write chunk to push
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Copy a Write chunk from the Call transport header to the
Reply transport header. Update each segment's length field
to reflect the number of bytes written in that segment.

Return values:
On success, returns length in bytes of the Reply XDR buffer
that was consumed by the Write chunk
-EMSGSIZE on XDR buffer overflow
